{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> χρῆμα</b>, ατος, τό: <br /> (χράομαι):— <b>need,</b> in the phrase παρὰ χ. or παραχρῆμα (which see); <b>a thing that one needs</b> or <b>uses,</b>[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"compare 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Oeconomicus” 1.9f (_plural_)\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: hence in <i>plural</i>, <b>goods, property</b> (χρήματα λέγομεν πάντα ὅσων ἡ ἀξία νομίσματι μετρεῖται [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Ethica Nicomachea” 1119b26), 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 2.78, 203, +others (never in 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad”), 8th-7th c.BC: Hesiodus Epicus “Opera et Dies” 320, 407, etc. \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; of temple-<b>treasures, heirlooms,</b> etc., [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “Mnemos.” 57.208 (Argos, 6th c.BC)\">Refs 6th c.BC+</a>]; τὰ ἱρὰ χ. τῆς Ἀθηναίης [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 2.28, compare 9.81; θησαυρούς.. ἄλλα τε χρύσεα ἄφατα χ. [prev. author] 7.190; πολλῶν χ. ἐξαίρετον ἄνθος 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Agamemnon” 954; πειρῶ τὸν πλοῦτον χρήματακαὶ κτήματα κατασκευάζειν· ἔστι δὲ χ. μὲν τοῖς ἀπολαύειν ἐπισταμένοις, κ. δὲ τοῖς κτᾶσθαι δυναμένοις 5th-6th c.BC: Isocrates Orator 1.28; τοῖς σκεύεσι καὶ τοῖς χρήμασιν ἀποθήκη 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 6.97 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; πρόβατα καὶ ἄλλα χ. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Anabasis” 5.2.4; τὰ ἀνδράποδα.. καὶ χρήματα τὰ πλεῖστα ἀπέδρα αὐτούς [prev. work] 7.8.12: proverbial, χρήματα ψυχὴ πέλεται.. βροτοῖσι\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>] a man's <b>money</b> is his life, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th-7th c.BC: Hesiodus Epicus “Opera et Dies” 686 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; χρήματ᾽ ἄνηρ '<b>money</b> makes the man', [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 7th-6th c.BC: Alcaeus Lyricus 49, 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “I.” 2.11; ἐν χρήμασιν οἰκεῖ πατρώοις 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Eumenides” 757, compare “Ch.” 135; also χρημάτων πένητες 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Electra” 37; τὰ χρήματ᾽ ἐνεχυράζομαι 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Nubes” 241; χρήματα πορίζειν [prev. author] “Ec.” 236; ἄτιμοι ἦσαν τὰ σώματα, τὰ δὲ χ. εἶχον 5th-6th c.BC: Andocides Orator 1.74; χρημάτων ἥσσων 3rd c.AD: Democritus Epigrammaticus 50; χρημάτων κρείσσων 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 2.60; χρήμασι νικώμενος [prev. passage]; χρημάτων ἀδωρότατος [prev. work] 65; ἐλπίδα χρήμασιν ὠνητήν [prev. author] 3.40; μήτε χρημάτων φειδομένους μήτε πόνων 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Phaedo” 78a; ζημιοῦσθαι χρήμασιν [prev. author] “Lg.” 721b \">Refs 7th c.BC+</a>]; even of debts, διαλῦσαι τὰ χ. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 20.12; δεθέντ᾽ ἐπὶ χρήμασιν ἐν τῷ δεσμωτηρίῳ [prev. author] 24.168.—Acc. to 2nd c.AD(?): Pollianus Epigrammaticus 9.87 the _Ionic dialect_ used also the _sing._ in this sense, and so we find, ἐπὶ κόσῳ ἂν χρήματι.. \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; for how much <b>money</b>.. ? Answ. ἐπ᾽ οὐδενί, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 3.38; ταύτην (i.e. τὴν χλανίδα) πωλέω μὲν οὐδενὸς χ. δίδωμι δὲ ἄλλως [prev. work] 139 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; also in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 6th c.BC: Theognis Elegiacus 197 \">Refs 6th c.BC+</a>], χ. δ᾽ ὃ μὲν Διόθεν καὶ σὺν δίκῃ ἀνδρὶ γένητα; in <i>Attic dialect</i>, οὐδενὸς ἂν χ. δεξάμενοι at no <b>price,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Andocides Orator 2.4 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; and in later Prose, <b>fund, sum of money, Arch. f. Religionswiss.</b>[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 10.211 (Cos, 2nd c.BC)\">Refs 2nd c.BC+</a>]; τὸ πλῆθος τοῦ χ. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st c.BC: Diodorus Siculus Historicus 13.106, cf. NT.Act.4.37, 2nd c.AD: Lucianus Sophista “VH” 1.20; χρήματα \">NT+1st c.BC+</a>]<b>merchandise,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st c.AD(?): Heraclitus 90, 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Historia Graeca (Hellenica)” 1.6.37, 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 3.74 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; <b>property, substance,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" Berl.Sitzb. 1927.161 (from Cyrene). \">Refs</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> generally, <b>thing, matter, affair,</b> especially in <i>Epic dialect</i> and <i>Ionic dialect</i>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “hymnus ad Mercurium” 332, 8th-7th c.BC: Hesiodus Epicus “Opera et Dies” 344, 402; χρημάτων ἄελπτον οὐδέν 7th c.BC: Archilochus Lyricus 74; πάντων χ. δικαιότατον 6th c.BC: Mimnermus Lyricus 8; πρῶτον χρημάτων πάντων 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 7.145 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; ἀντὶ πάντων χ. on every <b>account,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Andocides Orator 2.21; δεινότατον ἁπάντων χρημάτων [prev. work] 1 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; πᾶν χ. ἐκίνεε 'left no stone unturned', [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 5.96 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; τεκμαίρει χρῆμ᾽ ἕκαστον 'deeds show the man', [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “O.” 6.74; πάντων χ. μέτρον ἄνθρωπος 5th c.BC: Protagoras Philosophus 1 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; περαίνεται τὸ χ. the <b>issue</b> is being decided, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus “Caesar” 47 \">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]: <i>plural</i>, simply, <b>things,</b> ὁμοῦ πάντα χ. ἦν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Anaxagoras Philosophus 1, compare 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Cratylus” 440a, “Euthd.” 294d, 3rd c.AD: Plotinus Philosophus 4.2.1. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.2</b></Level3> χρῆμα is frequently expressed where it might be omitted, δεινὸν χ. ἐποιεῦντο [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 8.16; οἷόν τι χ. ποιήσειε [prev. work] 138 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ἐς ἀφανὲς χ. ἀποστέλλειν ἀποικίην to send out a colony without any certain <b>destination,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] 4.150 \">Refs</a>]; frequently in Trag., τί χρῆμ; ={τί}; <b>what?</b> τί χ. λεύσσ; [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Prometheus Vinctus” 300, “Ch.” 10 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; or <b>why?</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Alcestis” 512 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; so in <i>genitive</i>, τοῦ χ. (i.e. ἕνεκα); [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Nubes” 1223; τί χ. δρᾷ; 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Ajax” 288, compare “Ph.” 1231; τί χ. πάσχε; 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Hippolytus” 909 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; τί δ᾽ ἐστὶ χρῆμ; what is <b>the matter?</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Choephori” 885; πικρόν τί μοι δοκεῖ χ. εἶναι 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Gorgias” 485b; ἡδύ [prev. author] “Tht.” 209e, +others\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; μάλιστα χρημάτων most <b>of anything,</b> i. e. <b>certainly,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" Anonymus “Oxy.” 1611.68 (3rd c.AD);compare χρέος 11.2. \">Refs 3rd c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.3</b></Level3> used in periphrases to express something strange or extraordinary of its kind, ὑὸς χ. μέγα a huge <b>monster</b> of a boar, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 1.36; ἦν τοῦ χειμῶνος χ. ἀφόρητον [prev. author] 7.188 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; τὸ χ. τῶν νυκτῶν ὅσον what a <b>business</b> the nights are! [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Nubes” 2 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; λιπαρὸν τὸ χ. τῆς πόλεως what a grand city! [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “Av.” 826, compare “Lys.” 83 \">Refs</a>]; κλέπτον τὸ χ. τἀνδρός a thievish <b>sort</b> of fellow, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “V.” 933; τὸ χ. τοῦ νοσήματος [prev. author] “Lys.” 1085 \">Refs</a>]; μακάριον.. λέγεις τυράννου χ. your tyrant-<b>creature,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Respublica” 567e; χ. θαυμαστὸν γυναικός 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus “Antonius” 31 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: without a <i>genitive</i>, ἔλαφον, καλόν τι χ. καὶ μέγα [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Institutio Cyri (Cyropaedia)” 1.4.8 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; σοφόν τοι χρῆμ᾽ ἄνθρωπος truly a clever <b>creature</b> is he! [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 3rd c.BC: Theocritus Poeta Bucolicus 15.83 \">Refs 3rd c.BC+</a>]; κοῦφον χ. ποιητής ἐστιν καὶ πτηνὸν καὶ ἱερόν, of the poet, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Ion” 534b \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; χ. καλόν τι such a fine <b>thing!</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 3rd c.BC: Theocritus Poeta Bucolicus 15.23 \">Refs 3rd c.BC+</a>]; also in a periphrastic use, οὐδὲν χ. τοῦ ἀγκῶνος κάμψαι δύνανται cannot bend the elbow <b>at all,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Hippocrates Medicus “περὶ ἀγμῶν” 42. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level4><b>__II.3.b</b></Level4> so, to express a great number or mass, as we say, <b>a deal, a heap of</b>.., πολλόν τι χ. τῶν τέκνων, χ. πολλὸν ἀρδίων, νεῶν, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 3.109, 4.81, 6.43; χ. πολλόν τι χρυσοῦ [prev. author] 3.130; σμικρὸν τὸ χ. τοῦ βίου 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Supplices” 953 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ὅσον τὸ χ. παρνόπων what a <b>lot</b> of locusts! [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Acharnenses” 150; ὅσον τὸ χ. τοῦ πλακοῦντος [prev. author] “Eq.” 1219; πολὺ χ. τεμαχῶν [prev. author] “Pl.” 894 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; τὸ χ. τῶν κόπων ὅσον what a <b>lot</b> of them! [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “Ra.” 1278; τῶν λαμπάδων ὅσον τὸ χ. [prev. author] “Th.” 281 \">Refs</a>]; also of persons, χ. θηλειῶν woman<b>kind,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Phoenissae” 198; σφενδονητῶν πάμπολύ τι χ. 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Institutio Cyri (Cyropaedia)” 2.1.5; μέγα χ. Λακαινᾶν 3rd c.BC: Theocritus Poeta Bucolicus 18.4: without a _genitive_, ὅσον τὸ χ. ἐπὶ δεῖπνον ἦλθε\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>] what a <b>crowd</b>.. ! [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Pax” 1192. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__III</b></Level2> (χράω (B) A) <b>oracle,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Empedocles Poeta Philosophus 115.1. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]","strongNumber":"G5536","accentedUnicode":"χρῆμα","relatedNos":[{"strongNumber":"G0888","matchingForm":"ἀχρεῖος","stepTransliteration":"achreios","gloss":"worthless","_zh_tw_Gloss":"無用","_es_Gloss":"inútil","_zh_Gloss":"无用"},{"strongNumber":"G2173","matchingForm":"εὔχρηστος","stepTransliteration":"euchrēstos","gloss":"helpful","_zh_tw_Gloss":"都有益處, 有益處","_es_Gloss":"útil","_zh_Gloss":"都有益处, 有益处"},{"strongNumber":"G5537","matchingForm":"χρηματίζω","stepTransliteration":"chrēmatizō","gloss":"to announce","_zh_tw_Gloss":"稱為, 警戒","_es_Gloss":"anunciar","_zh_Gloss":"称为, 警戒"},{"strongNumber":"G5539","matchingForm":"χρήσιμος","stepTransliteration":"chrēsimos","gloss":"profitable","_zh_tw_Gloss":"益處","_es_Gloss":"provechoso","_zh_Gloss":"益处"},{"strongNumber":"G5543","matchingForm":"χρηστός","stepTransliteration":"chrēstos","gloss":"good/kind","_zh_tw_Gloss":"恩慈","_es_Gloss":"bueno/amable","_zh_Gloss":"恩慈"}],"shortDef":"money, wealth, possessions","mediumDef":"money, wealth, possessions <br /><b>anything useful,</b> or <b>needful;</b> <i>plural</i> <b>wealth, riches,</b> <ref='Mrk.10.23'>Mk. 10:23</ref>; <ref='Luk.18.24'>Lk. 18:24</ref>; <b>money,</b> <ref='Act.8.18, 20; 24.26'>Acts 8:18, 20; 24:26</ref>; <i>singular</i> <b>price,</b> <ref='Act.4.37'>Acts 4:37</ref>*","stepGloss":"money","stepTransliteration":"chrēma","count":7,"_es_Definition":"en la mayoría de los casos pl. posesiones, riqueza, recursos ; dinero ; sg. dinero, ganancia (HCH.4:37)","_zh_tw_Definition":"1) 財富, 產業<br>2) 貨幣 (徒 4:37,8:18.20,24:26)","_zh_Definition":"1) 财富, 产业<br>2) 货币 (徒 4:37,8:18.20,24:26)","_step_Type":"word","_vi_Definition":"tiền; sự giàu có","_zh_tw_Gloss":"錢, 錢財","_es_Gloss":"dinero","_zh_Gloss":"钱, 钱财"}]}